  m_text: "Terms and Conditions\L\Lfor Logic Labyrinth\L\LThese Terms and Conditions
    (\u201CTerms\u201D) govern the use of the Logic Labyrinth desktop application
    (\u201Cthe Game\u201D), an educational game designed to enhance learning and
    understanding of digital logic concepts. By installing or using the Game, users
    agree to comply with the following terms.\L\L1. Acceptance of Terms\L\LBy accessing,
    installing, or playing Logic Labyrinth, you (\u201CUser\u201D or \u201CPlayer\u201D)
    agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, you must not install or
    use the Game.\L\L2. Ownership and License\L\L2.1 License Grant\LThe Logic Labyrinth
    development team grants you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license
    to install and use the Game for personal, non-commercial, educational purposes
    only.\L\L2.2 Ownership\LAll rights, title, and interest in the Game\u2014including
    its source code, design, graphics, content, and materials\u2014remain the property
    of the Logic Labyrinth development team. Unauthorized reproduction, distribution,
    or modification of the Game is strictly prohibited.\L\L2.3 Platform Limitation\LThe
    Game is designed for Windows 10/11 (64-bit) desktop and laptop devices only.
    It may not function correctly on other operating systems or platforms.\L\L3.
    User Accounts and Data\L\L3.1 Account Creation\LSome features of the Game may
    require user registration. You are responsible for keeping your login credentials
    secure and for all activities performed under your account.\L\L3.2 Data Storage\LThe
    Game may store player progress, level completion, and scores locally or through
    a database connection. The development team strives to maintain data integrity
    but does not guarantee that data will always be available or error-free.\L\L3.3
    Age Restriction\LThe Game is recommended for users aged 13 and above (PG rating).
    By using the Game, you confirm that you meet this requirement or have parental/guardian
    consent.\L\L4. In-Game Purchases\L\L4.1 Free-to-Play Access\LAll core features
    of Logic Labyrinth are free to ensure accessibility for students and educators.\L\L4.2
    Optional Purchases\LThe Game may include optional in-game purchases such as stronger
    flashlights, additional health, or extra hints to assist players during gameplay.
    These features are entirely optional and do not affect the main learning experience.\L\L4.3
    Payment Methods\LPayments for optional items can be made securely through supported
    digital payment platforms such as GCash and Maya. All payments are one-time and
    non-refundable, except as required by applicable laws.\L\L5. User Responsibilities\L\LUsers
    agree not to:\L\LUse the Game for unlawful purposes.\L\LAttempt to modify, hack,
    or exploit the Game\u2019s systems or data.\L\LShare or distribute unauthorized
    copies of the Game.\L\LEngage in cheating or unfair manipulation of game features.\L\LFailure
    to comply may result in the suspension or termination of access to the Game.\L\L6.
    Limitations and Disclaimers\L\L6.1 Academic Nature\LLogic Labyrinth is an academic
    project developed for educational use. The team provides limited maintenance
    and technical support within the project\u2019s defined duration.\L\L6.2 System
    Limitations\L\LThe Game is single-player only and currently does not support
    multiplayer functions.\L\LLeaderboard data may not be updated in real time and
    may refresh periodically (e.g., every two weeks).\L\LThe Game requires a local
    or hosted database connection (MySQL) for saving progress.\L\LVisuals and performance
    may vary depending on device specifications.\L\L6.3 Disclaimer of Warranties\LThe
    Game is provided \u201Cas is\u201D without any express or implied warranties.
    The Logic Labyrinth team does not guarantee uninterrupted or error-free operation
    and shall not be held liable for data loss or system malfunctions.\L\L7. Support
    and Updates\L\LThe team provides up to two months of post-deployment support
    for bug fixes, troubleshooting, and user guidance. After this period, support
    will be on a best-effort basis and is not guaranteed.\L\LUpdates or improvements
    may be released at the discretion of the development team.\L\L8. Amendments\L\LThe
    Logic Labyrinth team reserves the right to update or modify these Terms at any
    time. Significant changes will be communicated through appropriate channels.
    Continued use of the Game after revisions constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.\L\L9.
    Termination\L\LThe development team may suspend or terminate access to the Game
    at any time for users who violate these Terms or misuse the system.\L\L10. Contact
    Information\L\LFor inquiries, feedback, or technical support, users may contact
    the Logic Labyrinth development team through their official communication channels
    as indicated in the project documentation.\L\LAcknowledgment\L\LBy using or installing
    Logic Labyrinth, you confirm that you have read, understood, and agreed to these
    Terms and Conditions."
